## Project: Aquacanvas

AI-powered photo-to-art e-commerce platform. Users upload a photo, choose an art style (watercolor, oil painting, etc.), and receive a transformed artwork they can order as a print.

## Required reading at session start

1. `ROADMAP.md` — Project status, current sprint, completed work. Update after completing work.
2. `TECHSTACK.md` — Decided stack, versions, project structure. Do not deviate.
3. `brand_assets/DESIGN.md` — Design system. All UI must follow it.

## Token efficiency

- Read only relevant sections of docs, not entire files unnecessarily.
- Keep code comments minimal — code should be self-documenting.
- Invoke only the skill relevant to the current task.
- Update ROADMAP.md at session end, not after every small change.
3. `.cursor/skills/` — Invoke the relevant skill before writing code:
   - `frontend-design` — Before any UI work
   - `supabase-patterns` — Before database/auth/storage work
   - `component-scaffold` — Before creating new components
   - `i18n-patterns` — Before writing any user-facing text
   - `error-handling` — Before building data-fetching pages or form flows
   - `api-patterns` — Before writing Server Actions, Route Handlers, or data-fetching logic
   - `quality-review` — After completing any feature/page/refactor. Final quality gate.

## Core constraints

- Next.js 16.x App Router + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4 via @tailwindcss/postcss
- **Shadcn/UI for all UI primitives** — Button, Input, Card, Label, Avatar, Separator, Textarea, Progress, Badge, Switch, AlertDialog, Skeleton. Never raw HTML. Custom variants in `src/components/ui/` match DESIGN.md. After installing a new Shadcn component (`npx shadcn@latest add <name>`), immediately customize it to match DESIGN.md before using it. **Caution:** Shadcn install may overwrite existing customized components — always verify with `git diff` after install and restore any reverted customizations.
- Supabase for backend (PostgreSQL, Auth, Storage, Edge Functions)
- Server Components by default — `'use client'` only when required
- Design tokens from DESIGN.md — never default Tailwind colors
- **Theme-aware colors only**: `text-foreground` (not `text-white`), `bg-surface-dim` (not `bg-black`), `text-muted-foreground` (not `text-white/50`). All colors resolve via CSS variables for dark/light mode. `next-themes` with `ThemeProvider` in root layout.
- Typography: `font-heading` + `font-sans` — never verbose arbitrary font syntax
- kebab-case files, PascalCase exports
- Zod for validation, Zustand for client state, TanStack Query for server state
- All user-facing strings via next-intl (`messages/en.json`) — never hardcoded. `NextIntlClientProvider` wraps root layout.

## AI / Image generation constraints

- **Server-side only** — AI API-calls (Replicate, OpenAI, etc.) happen exclusively in Server Actions or Edge Functions. Never call AI APIs from the client.
- **Lazy SDK initialization** — `getReplicate()` or `getOpenAI()` as lazy singletons. Never instantiate at module scope.
- **Cost tracking** — Log every AI API call with cost estimate. Implement per-user rate limits.
- **Async processing** — Image generation is async. Use polling or webhooks for status. Show progress UI to the user.
- **Storage flow** — Original photo → Supabase Storage. Generated image → Supabase Storage. Both linked to the order record.

## Security standards

- Env vars: use `src/lib/env.ts` getters — never `process.env.VAR!`. Exception: `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` must use inline `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_*!` because Next.js bundler requires static string access.
- **Lazy SDK initialization**: Server-only SDK clients (Stripe, Replicate, Resend, etc.) must use lazy singletons — never instantiate at module scope.
- All Server Actions: Zod validation before processing, return `ActionResult<T>`, never expose raw DB errors. **Never `as string` on `formData.get()`** — always Zod-parse. **All ID params must pass `z.string().uuid()`** before use in queries. **Error strings must be i18n keys** from the `errors` namespace, never hardcoded English. Client components translate via `useActionError()` hook.
- **HTML ↔ Zod alignment**: HTML input attributes (`min`, `max`, `type`, `pattern`) must match Zod schema constraints.
- File uploads: send files as FormData to Server Actions. Validate size + MIME type server-side, upload to Supabase Storage via server client. Storage path: `{user.id}/{purpose}/{orderId}.{ext}`. Never expose Storage credentials to the client.
- Open redirect prevention: validate redirect URLs against allowlist.
- OAuth redirectTo: always `${env.siteUrl}/auth/callback`.
- Role-based routing: read role from `user.app_metadata.role` (JWT) — never DB queries in middleware.
- Admin reads/writes: use `createClient()` (anon key) everywhere — RLS `is_admin()` policies grant full admin access. Only use `createAdminClient()` (service-role) for Supabase Auth Admin API calls.
- RLS admin policies: always use `public.is_admin()` SECURITY DEFINER function — never inline subqueries on profiles in RLS policies.

## Engineering standards

- **Confirm before coding.** Only start writing code when you are 95% confident that you and the user agree on what to build and the best approach. If there is any ambiguity — about requirements, architecture, trade-offs, or scope — stop and clarify first. It is always cheaper to discuss than to rewrite.
- **No workarounds.** Always solve problems properly. Diagnose root cause first. If stuck, discuss with the user.
- **`revalidatePath`/`revalidateTag` only in mutations**: Never call during Server Component rendering. Only in Server Actions or Route Handlers.
- **Error boundaries required**: `error.tsx` at root and each route group level.
- **Avoid N+1 queries**: Never query inside a loop. Batch with `Promise.all` + `.in()`.
- **No string-interpolated PostgREST subqueries**: Fetch related IDs first, then filter.

## High-priority cross-cutting concerns

- **SEO**: Every page needs `generateMetadata` with title/description from locale files. Public pages require JSON-LD (`Product`, `Organization`), Open Graph, hreflang. `sitemap.ts` + `robots.ts` in `src/app/`.
- **a11y (WCAG 2.1 AA)**: Skip-to-content link, `<main id="main-content">`, one visible h1, keyboard nav, `role="alert"` on errors, `aria-invalid`+`aria-describedby` on fields, `prefers-reduced-motion` respected, no `href="#"`.
- **i18n**: All strings via `useTranslations` (client) / `getTranslations` (server). `generateMetadata` uses translations. Client-side validation errors and `aria-label` values must also use translations.
